the british broadcasting corp plans to launch a 
24hour service in czechoslovakia this weekend the first of its 
kind in eastern europe a bbc official says 
bbc world service programs are rebroadcast by radio stations in 
several east european nations but czechoslovakia is the first to 
allocate the bbc a domestic frequency 
andrew taussig european controller at the bbc world service 
says prague and bratislava will receive the first service 
broadcasts to the city of brno will start in the next few days he 
says 
coming after more than 50 years this is an historic moment 
for the bbc and for our listeners as we deploy for the first time 
on local soil a 24hour service in english and local languages 
said taussig 
the programs will be a mixture of bbc world service items in 
czech slovak and english 
the world service financed by the government is broadcast 
around the world in many languages and reaches about 120 million 
listeners 
</TEXT>
