<TEXT>
the european community environment 
ministers have decided to ban the production and use of 
ozoneharming chlorofluorocarbons by mid1997 officials say 
by jan 1 1992 the 12nation trade bloc will cut in half 
production and importation of the manmade chemical often used as an 
aerosol propellant it will be outlawed by july 7 1997 officials 
said friday 
chlorofluorocarbons are believed to deplete the ozone layer 
which protects the earth from ultraviolet radiation from the sun 
the ec commission is studying the possibility including a tax on 
chlorofluorocarbons to speed up the ban 
international agreements seek to ban chlorofluorocarbons by the 
year 2000 
</TEXT>
