<TEXT>
a ferry capsized and sank in rough 
mediterranean waters early today while taking about 100 american 
sailors from christmas shore leave back to the aircraft carrier uss 
saratoga at least 19 drowned 
american and israeli rescue teams searched throughout the night 
for others feared missing after the israeli ferry tuvia went under 
shortly after midnight in windy choppy seas about 200 yards from 
the saratoga the us ship was about a mile off the coast 
fortyseven sailors were hospitalized and 38 rescued unharmed 
from the choppy seas according to stateowned israel radio it 
said four were in serious condition and most of the others had been 
released later in the morning 
it was the deadliest accident involving american servicemen 
taking part in the usled multinational force arrayed against 
iraq and raised the number of americans killed in operation desert 
shield to at least 73 
the sailors were among hundreds who spent their holiday liberty 
friday in haifa some with wives and girlfriends who had flown from 
home to meet them 
the saratoga has a crew of about 4500 
a haifa police spokesman chaim avinoam said 19 bodies had been 
recovered by midmorning army spokesman ranaan gissen said six of 
the bodies were found trapped in the twodeck 57foot ferry about 
80 feet below the surface of the mediterranean 
officials said at midafternoon that two other sailors still 
could be missing saratoga commanders recalled all 1920 men from 
shore leave 
there was no official report on the cause of the sinking 
witnesses said they believed there were too many people in the back 
of the ferry 
shaul raziel director of the israel port authority said a 
combination of events probably caused the accident the seating 
or movement in one direction a sudden wave and the disaster 
happened he said on army radio 
