with top kremlin officials speaking last week of 
the dangers of dictatorship and bloodshed world leaders wondered 
whether the soviets would stumble on their way out of the cold war 
era 
the stunning resignation of foreign minister eduard a 
shevardnadze on thursday was the strongest signal yet that the 
reforms that he and soviet president mikhail s gorbachev began 
nearly six years ago have run off the rails 
dictatorship is coming shevardnadze warned from the 
