dates are the iraqis favorite winter fruit but they have 
rarely tried to turn them into desserts 
now though confectionaries are now making datebased sweets 
instead of the traditional richer sweets that require plenty of 
sugar flour and fat to make 
the younger generations have heard about a delicacy called 
madgoga from their grandmothers but a few have tasted the sweet 
madgoga is cheap and easy to make i wonder why we had 
forgotten it and have only remembered our best traditional sweets 
in this hour of crisis said abdul hussein jawad whose family is 
a wellknown baghdad sweetmaker 
jawad said he makes madgoga by adding sesame paste to ground 
dates sometimes he adds nuts and coconuts to make it tastier and 
more nourishing 
dates and milk constituted the staple diet of bedouin tribes in 
the desert mainly because the fruit is rich in vitamins and milk 
prevents dehydration 
madgoga was rediscovered after sweets shops were forced to close 
in the wake of international sanctions that followed the aug 2 
invasion of kuwait 
the embargo has forced the government to ration food items 
including cooking oil flour milk and sugar these items have 
disappeared from the markets but families receive limited 
