here is a brief chronology of important 
events in the life of lech walesa who was sworn in saturday as the 
first popularly elected president of poland 
 
december 1970 an electrician at lenin shipyward in gdansk 
walesa helps lead his first strike when protests over food price 
increases sweep the baltic ports dozens are shot by security 
police walesa is arrested and temporarily dismissed from his job 
1976 shipyard again dismisses walesa for criticizing 
communistlinked union 
1978 unemployed because of his activism walesa begins 
organizing free trade unions independent of the communist party 
august 1980 walesa jumps the fence of the lenin shipyard to 
take charge of a strike eventually signing agreements with the 
communist government creating solidarity the first independent 
trade union in the sovietbloc leads the union through tumultuous 
months as new freedoms sweep poland and discontent with the 
communist regime grows 
dec 13 1981 is interned under martial law released in 
november 1982 
december 1983 is awarded nobel peace prize but does not go to 
oslo to collect it for fear he will not be allowed to reenter 
poland 
may and august 1988 waves of strikes combined with rising 
social discontent and a collapsing economy force the communist 
regime to make its first overtures to solidarity 
april 1989 solidarity is restored to legal status 
june 1989 in partially free parliament elections soldidarity 
wins all but one seat available to it 
august 1989 walesa proposes tadeusz mazowiecki as the first 
noncommunist prime minister in the east bloc 
dec 9 1990 after a volatile campaign walesa wins the 
presidency by a 31 margin 
dec 22 1990 walesa is sworn in as president 
 
