<TEXT>
france is asking unified germany for reparations 
from world war ii that the former east germany had balked at 
paying an official said saturday 
the official confirming a newspaper report said the move was 
in line with october unification of the two germanys which gives 
the united country the burden of various debts of the former east 
germany 
in paris an authorized source speaking on condition of 
anonymity also confirmed discussions were under way but stressed 
they involved claims from private citizens not french governmental 
claims 
die welt newspaper quoted reliable sources saying french 
diplomats had spoken several times with the foreign ministry in 
bonn about the issue and the french embassy in bonn had sent two 
written notes to the ministry 
a ministry spokesman who refused to be identified by name said 
the issue was a normal occurrence after unification about which 
there must be negotiations france had previously been in contact 
with east germany about reparations he said 
the die welt report said france had put its claim in the 
currencies of 1945 376 billion french francs and 261 billion 
reichsmarks the currency of nazi germany asked how the claims 
would be converted into todays money the spokesman said it was a 
technical question for negotiators 
in the west german currency reform of 1948 10 reichsmarks were 
converted to 1 mark at that rate the german currency part of the 
french claim would be set at 261 billion marks today worth about 
17 billion 
the french currency also has been reformed since the war data 
on its conversion were not available 
according to one estimate the final claim could rise over 65 
billion 
the spokesman said there would be talks early next year about 
the issue 
when the two germanys united in october the federal government 
assumed the debts and treaty obligations of east germany which 
unlike west germany had not paid reparations to the western allies 
after the war the big four allies the united states france 
britain and the soviet union assessed reparations against germany 
to be paid in assets and capital goods 
but germany was economically prostrate and collection of 
reparations was uneven at the same time the united states was 
pouring billions into west germany and other european countries in 
the marshall plan which helped revive wardamaged economies 
the london agreement of 1953 among west germany and the four 
allies permitted the reparations question to remain open until a 
final settlement of wartime issues which has finally happened in 
the past year with the unification of germany and the paris summit 
in november of 34 countries that sought to draw the final curtain 
over world war ii 
die welt said some of the damages france was claiming had 
occurred when frenchowned property was seized in the soviet 
occupation zone which became east germany other claims were 
related to forced labor by prisoners of war restitutions for 
seized jewelry and valuable objects die welt said 
in the mid1980s west germany agreed to pay damages to some 
french people who did forced labor or were drafted into the germany 
military 
germany is paying reparations to israel and individual jews for 
the holocaust that sum so far has totaled about 80 billion marks 
about 53 billion at todays exchange rates 
jewish organizations were unsuccessful over the years in 
pressing east germany for reparations as the communist government 
refused to accept any war guilt from the nazi era 
in another bill from postwar days germany is paying the soviets 
about 29 billion marks or 195 billion in grants and credits to 
cover the costs of withdrawing 360000 soviets troops from former 
east germany the old soviet occupation zone over the next four 
years 
