the wooden buildings were splintered and desks strewn around the 
campus where trees were twisted and not just blown down he said 
ada said a preliminary survey by federal emergency management 
agency teams found 341 homes destroyed 460 with major damage and 
1210 with minor damage to the point they were uninhabitable 
