<TEXT>
stanford university under fire for 
claiming faculty discounts on game tickets are researchrelated 
expenses has agreed to temporarily cut its billing rate to the 
government by 2 percent 
the decrease is part of a provisional agreement drafted 
during talks last week between stanford administrators and a team 
of contract experts and administrators from the office of naval 
research one of three federal agencies investigating stanfords 
billing of research overhead costs 
the navy is looking into claims that the school may have 
overbilled the government as much as 200 million in the past 
decade 
the interim agreement permits business relationships to be put 
on an orderly basis while the investigations continue said 
stanford spokesman larry horton 
stanford was charging the government 74 percent above the cost 
of a research contract to pay for overhead costs 
overhead costs include electricity bills building depreciation 
administrative expenses and the use of campus libraries and other 
facilities by researchers under government contract the government 
allows those expenses 
but stanford also contends that fringe benefits for its faculty 
such as discounts on football and basketball tickets swimming 
pools tennis courts and gyms are ordinary costs of doing business 
and includes them in research overhead charges 
under the temporary contract the university will be reimbursed 
at 72 percent until june 1991 when the navy investigation is 
expected to be completed 
based on what the probes find the billing rate may change 
in exchange for stanfords temporary billing rate pullback the 
head of the fivemember navy team approved payment of 38 million 
in research bills that the office of naval research had refused to 
release since october 
stanford also agreed to reopen talks on memorandums of 
understanding that have guided its billing practices for 
government research during the past 30 years some government 
officials say the rates set in the documents may have unduly 
benefited stanford at the expense of taxpayers 
</TEXT>
